 department has been sealed at the hospital.\n\n\u201cAs many 71 individuals including doctors and nurses have tested positive for coronavirus at Bir Hospital\u201d, Dr Senchuri told Khabarhub, adding, \u201cOutpatient department has been closed for two days after the infection increased among the staffers at the hospital.\u201d\n\nContact tracing and disinfection jobs will be done during the closure of the OPD service, added Senchuri.\n\nHowever, emergency ward, laboratory and operation theatre services will remain open during the period.","title":"71 medical persons, health workers infected with COVID-19 at Bir Hospital - Khabarhub","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2020/02/124383/","video":[]}
